{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"647497f5-71aa-45d3-afca-c0a7d98ab195","content":"Here's what you need:\n\n**Environment variables** — tell the .NET NativeAOT runtime to invoke `createdump` on crash:\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"                          # Full dump (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\"  # %p=PID, %t=timestamp\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n    value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"      # Required for NativeAOT — runtime won't find it automatically\n```\n\n**Pod spec changes** — mount a volume so dumps survive container restarts, and ensure the process has `SYS_PTRACE` (needed by `createdump`):\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: my-app\n      # ... image, ports, etc.\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add: [\"SYS_PTRACE\"]\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: dump-volume\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: dump-volume\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi       # adjust based on expected dump size\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** is critical for NativeAOT — unlike CoreCLR, the runtime doesn't bundle or auto-locate `createdump`.\n- **`SYS_PTRACE`** is required because `createdump` uses `ptrace` to read process memory.\n- **`emptyDir`** is fine for transient collection; swap to a `PersistentVolumeClaim` if you need dumps to survive pod eviction.\n- Use `MiniDumpType=2` (Heap) instead of `4` (Full) to reduce dump size if full memory isn't needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5d895080-86d3-445a-9c3f-2e93a6e8954d","outputTokens":516,"requestId":"2C40:26FA86:16CDC2C:19B3236:69F94CFF"},"id":"10b1e507-1a95-4420-8e8e-aee8738c6f9f","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:51:06.348Z","parentId":"6562af62-c2f4-4a35-9516-c85cadaf8edb"}
